Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in physics would. What is the molecular formula of (E)-1-hydroperoxy-2-methylbut-1-ene?
Answer:
gpt_response:
The molecular formula of (E)-1-hydroperoxy-2-methylbut-1-ene can be determined by first identifying the structural formula of the compound. In this case, the compound consists of a 1-hydroperoxy-2-methylbut-1-ene moiety. 

The structural formula can be broken down into its constituent elements to determine the molecular formula. In this case, we have carbon (C), hydrogen (H), and oxygen (O) atoms. 

The molecular formula of (E)-1-hydroperoxy-2-methylbut-1-ene can be represented as C5H10O2.
